(b)\includegraphics[width=8cm]{f2b.eps}
\caption{(a) Maximum (bullets) and mean (open circles) melting rate of the ice disc as a function of the temperature of the plate.  (inset) Evolution of the experimental melting rate in function of time for different temperature from 5{$^\circ$C}  to 35{$^\circ$C}$\ $   by step of 5{$^\circ$C}  (see Legend). (b) Maximum (plain symbols) and mean (open symbols) melting rate of the ice disc as a function of the load $L$ at four temperatures 5{$^\circ$C}(triangles), 15{$^\circ$C}(diamonds), 25{$^\circ$C}(squares) and 35{$^\circ$C}(bullets).}


